Text.SourceString: Oh, you’re the new farmer.//I was worried there for a bit about a potential competitor.//<portrait=happy>Nothing to worry about, it seems.
<NPCName>Walter</> and I own the vineyard, you see. Our clients are mostly abroad.//<portrait=normal>Shall I send over a bottle?
Ugh… Every time I walk past that dumpster, I get a headache.
What are people putting in there? I thought we agreed to only put in clean, recyclable items.//<portrait=annoyed>Obviously, some people don’t know what clean means.
The dumpster is such an eyesore. We want to recycle, but there’s no place to do it.
How much longer are we going to let this pile up?
By the way, <NpcName>Ben</> sells seeds, too.//If <NpcName>Sam</> is ever closed, give <NpcName>Ben</> a try…
In fact, I buy a lot of things from him…//To help out his business a little, you see.
We save our own seeds. That’s the only way to get consistent quality.
The quality of the wine depends on the quality of the grapes.
The same goes for our sake.
We don’t sell to individuals—only businesses with liquor permits.
Now I eat homemade whenever I can.//<portrait=happy>To make up for the damage I did in my youth. Ha ha ha.
<NpcName>Dinda</>’s a dear friend of mine. She’s always so sweet.
Breakfast is very important, <PlayerName>$player</>. Don’t skip it!
In a way, farming is my therapy. I cultivate my plants and watch them grow.
To me, farming just feels…ah…soothing. Is it the same for you?
We should meet up and talk about farming sometimes… Since we both seem to be working in the same field now.//<portrait=happy>Oh! That’s a pun!
But please let’s keep it between us. We wouldn’t want anybody to get jealous.
By the way, <NpcName>Ben</> sells seeds, too.//If <NpcName>Sam</> is ever closed, give <NpcName>Ben</> a try…
In fact, I buy a lot of things from him…//To help out his business a little, you see.
Doing dishes is a chore, and it takes forever… To be perfectly honest, I’d rather cook all day.
In a way, farming is my therapy. I cultivate my plants and watch them grow.
To me, farming just feels…ah…soothing. Is it the same for you?
Playing farmer in this little town is so much fun… A lot more fun than playing the wife in the big city.
I always look forward to the town’s charming little holidays, too.
Doing dishes is a chore, and it takes forever…//<portrait=normal>To be perfectly honest, I’d rather cook all day.
Doing dishes is a chore, and it takes forever…//<portrait=normal>To be perfectly honest, I’d rather cook all day.
My Monday has been wonderful, thanks for asking. How's yours?//That’s good to hear, dear.
We make sure to have enough grapes to make wine year-round.
<NpcName>Taco</>’s a very independent pup. He likes to explore.//Sometimes I worry about him getting lost.
But he always comes home.
It was my idea to move here. I told <NpcName>Walter</> to stop chasing wealth and start enjoying it instead.
Then we were blessed with <NpcName>Luke</> a year later.
We make sure to have enough grapes to make wine year-round.
<NpcName>Taco</>’s very happy. We’re so glad he came to live with us.
He has so many friends around town, you know.//I think his best friend is our neighbor <NpcName>Archie</>.
Have you settled in yet? Take your time, dear. I didn’t feel like this was home for years…//I felt comfortable right away, sure. But home? That’s always been hard for me.
It must be a shock to your system, moving here from a big city.
It was my idea to move here. I told <NpcName>Walter</> to stop chasing wealth and start enjoying it instead.
Then we were blessed with <NpcName>Luke</> a year later.
I usually don’t like getting my hands dirty, but I just feel better when I’m working with the earth…
<NpcName>Luke</> handles all the vineyard business except for the farming side of it.
He even does his own quality control to keep our standards high…//<portrait=normal>I’m very proud of him. He’ll do very well when he takes over.
My favorite style of painting has to be Impressionism.//<portrait=happy>The short, strong brush strokes really capture the essence of the subjects without getting bogged down in the details.
It really shows that something doesn’t have to be logical to be beautiful.
<NpcName>Walter</> can be stubborn sometimes, especially when it comes to big decisions.
But he isn’t half as pushy as some people. You know?
We don’t necessarily have to grow grapes all year round.//In the Winter, we focus on other aspects of the vineyard.
But it’s nice to know that we have an extra supply.
My favorite style of painting has to be Impressionism.//<portrait=happy>The short, strong brush strokes really capture the essence of the subjects without getting bogged down in the details.
It really shows that something doesn’t have to be logical to be beautiful.
If you collect wild vegetables, have a look around, dear. We have plenty growing around here.
You’re welcome to check often.
We don’t necessarily have to grow grapes all year round.//In the Winter, we focus on other aspects of the vineyard.
But it’s nice to know that we have an extra supply.
I heard about Pufferfish moving in. I’d rather not discuss it right now.
It’s a bit upsetting, isn’t it? We came here to this beautiful island, hoping to get away from big corporations.//Then a part of the past followed us.
I hope you enjoyed the New Year’s gathering, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Met your standard, I hope?
It was such a blast last week at the lake. It’s a great way to keep the community close.
I brought some bok choy, and nobody touched it. What is it with vegetables, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Is it just because they’re green?
Sometimes I do miss modeling… The glam, the people…//But I don’t miss all of it. Some of it was rough.
It was tiring… Moonlighting at nightclubs every night to make ends meet until I got my big break…//That was the plan, anyway.
Obviously, I never got my big break.//<portrait=normal>But that’s a story for another time.
You can grow grapes in the Fall… Are you planting some this year?
Looking for tips? Oh, I’d love to give you some.//<portrait=normal>You have to ferment rice in a keg for several days to make sake.
Farming is easier if you have automatic sprinklers…//But not everybody needs them.
If you only have a few rows of crops, you can probably do without them.
There was a period when <NpcName>Luke</> dyed his hair bright blue. Then, he grew it out really long…//<portrait=normal>No, no – without the blue dye.
Actually, it was more like he grew it out really tall…//<portrait=normal>I wish he’d kept that style. He looked very nice that way.
Oh no! It’s Winter already. I need to start getting ready for the annual feast.
Oh my! I’m glad your toes are all covered up and warm.
We certainly don’t want them to freeze. Great call!
Oh, it's hard to work in this weather.
I better hurry.
It’s been raining like this all day… *sigh*
I have to be somewhere… Please excuse me.
Oh, it is hard to work in this weather.
I better hurry.
It’s been raining like this all day… *sigh*
Oh no. You seem flushed, <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re coming down with a cold! Get some rest!
I have to be somewhere… Please excuse me.
Once, I went to this beautiful ski resort in a small town down south.//It looked exactly like this when it snowed.
Ah, dear! I’ll have to ask <NpcName>Luke</> to shovel the snow tomorrow…
Winter nights can be really lonely, don’t you think?//I think it’s the sense that the year is ending.
It makes you think about all the things you haven’t done.
Have you eaten, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Would you like some tea? Or coffee?
Are you looking for <NpcName>Taco</>?//He should be here somewhere.
I make my own bread when I can. <NpcName>Eva</>’s is a little too chewy. It’s not the best for soup.
In the Summer, I usually grill whatever fruit or vegetables I can find and just drizzle honey on them.
We have cold drinks in the fridge. Feel free!
Sorry about the mess! I haven’t straightened up.
I wasn’t expecting company.
The soil here is ideal for grapes…//And there’s the hills and just the right amount of sunlight.
<NpcName>Luke</> used to run around the vineyard when he was little, and he’d eat grapes until his stomach hurt. Ah, ha ha.
That boy has no self-control.
There aren’t a lot of wild fruits here, for some reason.
I always loved gardening… But who’d have thought I’d actually enjoy making a living out of it?
I was a little bored at home. There’s not much to do…
Not everyone can do woodwork. You need certain skills, plus, it’s labor intensive…
I’m just bringing over some baked goods…
And gossip a little about the townies, right, <NpcName>Dinda</>? Ha ha…
Live music in the evening is always a good idea.
Umm… I felt like dancing tonight, so I just skipped cooking dinner and came here instead…
*Snapping her fingers slightly off-beat*
Yummy… I wonder what <NpcName>Frank</> puts in this.
…I need to pick up some flour… Hmm…
I wonder what <NpcName>Eva</> puts in this insanely delicious cake.//I’m determined to find out her secret!
Ah, fresh flowers sound good, don’t they, <PlayerName>$player</>? They really cheer the place up.
It’s important to take care of yourself. It’s not selfish…//<portrait=happy>On the contrary, it can really improve your performance, and it’s good for your mood.
Sometimes, I just want to chop my hair off, but I probably won’t…//Ha ha ha! I don’t think it would suit me…
I guess I know where <NpcName>Luke</> gets his indecisiveness.
<NpcName>Walter</>’ll go wild if I come home with pink hair or something.
My Monday has been wonderful. How's yours?
Of course, things are easier if you have automatic sprinklers…//But not everybody needs them.
I have to take care of the seating and the secret friend list really soon.
I have to handwrite and mail out each and every one of them by Saturday!
Oh, it’s incredibly stressful!
I can’t comment on our caterer for the New Year's Eve event. It's going to be a surprise!
I’m keeping it a secret so everybody’s surprised.
I’m going to try a new recipe today…
Oh, dang! I ran out of basil. Let’s see if I can just cook it without it…
I wish <NpcName>Luke</> would worry less. He overthinks things sometimes.
What are you doing here, <PlayerName>$player</>? Picking up a new wall clock?
Aren’t they great? Maybe I’ll get one for the house myself.
Live music in the evening is always a good idea… *dances in her seat*
People used to stare at me when I was out with <NpcName>Walter</> back in the city.//This was way before we had <NpcName>Luke</>…
People don’t do that here. They see me as more than just <NpcName>Walter</>’s wife…//They see me as <NpcName>Bree</>.
Too bad <NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t sell off-season produce… I’m craving pumpkin soup.
I wonder if <NpcName>Ben</> is around… He might have some.
Too bad <NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t sell off-season produce… I’m craving baked sweet potatoes.
I wonder if <NpcName>Ben</> is around… He might have some.
It’s really time to get an herbal hair treatment, huh?//<portrait=annoyed>My hair feels so coarse… Blech!
I’m just getting my hair blown today, nothing fancy…//Something decent for a simple dinner tonight.
At home, of course.
New hairdo, <PlayerName>$player</>?
